  "body": "This PR adds the `go build` option `-i` that installs the packages that are dependencies of the target (to speed up future builds).\r\n\r\nThis was removed in #1179 because it caused problems when cross-compiling, when the install was being done on the incorrect (not native) path (this [comment](https://github.com/containerd/containerd/issues/1905#issuecomment-352911114) gives a clear example).\r\n\r\nThe [`GOHOSTOS`](https://golang.org/doc/install/source#environment) environment variable was added to the Makefile to detect when the build was being done against the native platform, and only then add the `-i` option.\r\n\r\nAlso the `GO_BUILD_FLAGS` variable was added to encapsulate this option (and possible future ones), instead of just hard coding it into the `go build` command. According to the [`go build`](https://golang.org/cmd/go/#hdr-Compile_packages_and_dependencies) documentation the `-i` option is not exactly a build flag (it's listed separately) but for the purposes of this PR it can be considered as such.\r\n\r\nAs noted in this [comment](https://github.com/containerd/containerd/issues/1905#issuecomment-350863217) this option won't be needed in [Go 1.10](https://tip.golang.org/doc/go1.10#build).\r\n\r\nSome simple commands to test the modification:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nGOOS=linux make -pn | grep \"go build\"\r\nGOOS=windows make -pn | grep \"go build\"\r\nGOOS=windows GOHOSTOS=linux make -pn | grep \"go build\"\r\nGOOS=windows GOHOSTOS=windows make -pn | grep \"go build\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nCloses #1905.",
